    "The Fokker-Planck equation ( 27) is then completed with the no-flux boundary conditions (16), where we take κ ≥ 2.",
    "Similarly to what done before, in Corollary 1 we will prove that if the initial distribution has a compact support, then the support of f (t, A, w) remain equi-bounded for any t > 0, and thus the choice of the boundary conditions is not restrictive.",
    "This also justifies the fact that in the derivation of the collisional operator Q c (f, f) given by (28), it is possible to neglect terms involving the factor ϵA, even though A itself is not bounded.",
    "For these reasons, from now on we shall always assume that the initial distribution has compact support.Remark 2.",
    "The partial equilibrium of the controlled model shares the same structure of the one determined for the original model (22)."
